author: CNN
description: House Speaker Mike Johnson would not guarantee a vote on Affordable Care Act subsidies, saying the House would need “to find a consensus” on a proposal. “We’re going to do in the House what we always do and that is a deliberative process. We’re going to have to find consensus on whatever, whatever the proposal is,” he told CNN's Jake Tapper. #CNN #News
title: Johnson on committing to ACA subsidies vote: 'We do a deliberative process'

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins asked President Donald Trump in the White House Monday to respond to Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene's (R-Georgia) comments that he should focus more on domestic issues rather than foreign policy.
title: Trump on Marjorie Taylor Greene: ‘She’s lost her way’

author: CNN
description: GOP leader Sen. John Thune said the chamber is “in a holding pattern” on next steps of the bill. While some senators are optimistic that they could get to a time agreement to speed up consideration of the legislation, any one senator can object and delay a final vote. The House will have to return and adopt the deal struck in the Senate before it is sent to Trump’s desk to be signed. #CNN #News
title: 'We need to pass the torch': Rep. Moulton calls for 'new leadership' for Dems in Senate

author: CNN
description: Less than a year after his lightning power grab, Syria’s president Ahmed Al-Sharaa is capping his transformation from jihadist to global statesman in a historic visit to the White House that says as much about the young leader as it does his push for his country’s diplomatic reinvention. CNN's Paula Hancocks reports.
title: Syria's leader: From a $10M bounty on his head to a White House guest

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump has pardoned a long list of his political allies for their support or involvement in alleged plans to overturn the 2020 presidential election, according to the Department of Justice’s Pardon Attorney Ed Martin. CNN’s Alayna Treene reports. #cnn #news #politics
title: Trump pardons Giuliani and others involved in efforts to overturn 2020 election

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump demanded Monday that all air traffic controllers “get back to work, NOW,” warning that those who don’t may face penalties while promising bonuses for those who have worked during the government shutdown.  #CNN #News
title: Trump issues threat to air traffic controllers who don’t go to work

author: CNN
description: The concept of having your own personal flying vehicle is now a reality, starting at $190,000. CNN's Nick Watt reports.
title: 'It looks wrong': CNN's Nick Watt watches a 'flying car' in action

author: CNN
description: CNN's Saskya Vandoorne speaks to an unexpected fashion icon -- the French teenager who became an internet sensation when he was caught on camera looking dapper close to police following the heist at the Louvre in Paris. #cnn #news
title: CNN tracks down French teenager in viral photo

author: CNN
description: President Trump is seeking at least $1B in damages from the BBC after the organization aired a version of his January 6, 2021 speech that spliced different sections together to make it sound as though Trump told crowds he would walk with them to the Capitol and "fight like hell." A BBC spokesperson told CNN that “we will review the letter and respond directly in due course.” CNN's Max Foster reports. #cnn #news #trump #bbc #lawsuit
title: Trump threatens BBC with $1B lawsuit

author: CNN
description: Former Republican Congressman Adam Kinzinger discusses the eight Senate Democrats who struck a deal with Republicans to end the government shutdown, while dropping the critical demand of a guaranteed extension of Obamacare subsidies. #cnn #shutdown #democratscave #adamkinzinger
title: Did Democrats cave? Hear what Adam Kinzinger thinks.

author: CNN
description:
Typhoon Fung-wong slings around suspension bridge in the eastern Philippines. The typhoon made landfall as a Category 3 equivalent hurricane.
#cnn #news
title: Typhoon slings suspension bridge in Philippines

author: CNN
description:
Eight Democrats broke with their party and struck a deal with Republicans to end the government shutdown in exchange for a future vote on extending enhanced Affordable Care Act subsidies, putting Congress on a path to end the longest shutdown in US history within days.

#cnn #news #us #government #shutdown
title: Why eight Democrats struck deal with GOP to end shutdown

author: CNN
description: In a pivotal move, the US Food and Drug Administration on Monday said it is taking steps to remove the lengthy “black box” warning on many hormone treatments for women with menopause symptoms — a shift expected to give women more options for treatment and generate a flood of new prescriptions.  #CNN #News
title: ‘Black box’ safety warning to be removed from hormone therapy for menopause

author: CNN
description: House Speaker Mike Johnson praised the Senate for reaching a deal to end the government shutdown and warned his members they will soon have to return to Washington.  #CNN #News
title: Speaker Johnson praises Senate for deal to reopen government

author: CNN
description: During an interview with journalist Luke Harding from The Guardian, the Ukrainian presidential palace lost power, highlighting the conditions in Kyiv following a series of power outages caused by a massive Russian aerial assault over the weekend. #cnn #zelensky #ukraine
title: Power cuts out during Zelensky interview

author: CNN
description: Three Chinese astronauts have been forced to extend their six-month stay in space over concerns that their return ship may have been hit by debris, China’s space agency said. No alternative date has been given for the return of the trio, who blasted off from the country’s Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region in April.
title: Astronauts stuck in space after debris hits ship

author: CNN
description: Flight delays and cancellations have surged amid a 40-day government shutdown, with over 4 million passengers affected. A Southwest pilot urged passengers to "call their senators," saying delays are costing airlines millions and grounding planes for hours. Officials warn Thanksgiving travel could nearly halt, threatening economic growth.
title: Frustrated pilot urges passengers to 'call their senator'

author: CNN
description: CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten examines a drop in US consumer sentiment and whether the public is blaming President Donald Trump for economic uncertainty.  #CNN #News
title: ‘Political nightmare fuel’: Enten on public’s view of economy under Trump

description: Abdul El-Sayed, a progressive Democrat running for the US Senate in Michigan, has quietly erased thousands of old social media posts — including a dozen tweets that championed the “defund the police” movement. CNN’s KFile senior editor Andrew Kaczynski reports. #CNN #News
title: Senate candidate is latest politician to scrub 'defund the police' posts

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump has pardoned a long list of his political allies for their support or involvement in alleged plans to overturn the 2020 presidential election, according to the Department of Justice’s Pardon Attorney, Ed Martin. The individuals listed in a proclamation, which Martin posted on X late Sunday, include high-profile figures like Trump lawyers Rudy Giuliani, Sidney Powell and the president’s former chief of staff, Mark Meadows, among dozens of others.  #CNN #News
title: Trump pardons Rudy Giuliani, others involved in efforts to overturn 2020 election

description: The Senate has voted 60-40 on a key step toward reopening the government. The vote came after a critical group of eight Senate Democratic centrists reached a deal with Senate GOP leaders and the White House in exchange for a future vote on extending enhanced Affordable Care subsidies.  #CNN #News
title: Senate advances deal to reopen government after Democrats strike deal to end shutdown
